    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ceremonial ball game played by Southeastern Native North American tribes. Players utilize two long, wooden rackets to either hit a single wooden post or pass through two posts with a ball; scoring and team size vary across communities. Has origins in the Mississippian period and continues to be played by Cherokee, Choctaw, and other Southeastern tribes in the present day. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
